I'll give it a look, certainly seems interesting.<p>One question though: at a cursory glance through the code, the author switches between normal PHP brace syntax:<p><pre><code>  if ($something) {
    // do something
  }
</code></pre>
and the alternative PHP brace-less syntax:<p><pre><code>  if ($something):
    // do something
  endif;
</code></pre>
Is there any reason for the inconsistency? I usually reserve the alternative syntax for templates since it integrates well with HTML and the normal syntax for the actual code.
